        <div class="feature">
        <h1>CareerCraft: Bridging Students and the Professional World</h1>
        <p><strong>Goal:</strong> EduBridge aims to close the gap between academic learning and the corporate world. It connects students with organizations offering the resources and opportunities necessary to meet industry requirements.</p>
        </div><br>
        <div class="feature">
            <h2>Industry Integrating Learning Outcomes</h2>
            <p>EduBridge will permit students to select specialization (e.g., software development, engineering, data science, etc.). In relation to their studies, the platform will present skills and competencies sought by employers and skill attainment gaps. It will propose learning pathways which comprise certificates, project-based learning, and workshops relevant to the current market.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
            <h2>Timely Job and Internship Requirements</h2>
            <p>Students will receive job and internship announcements from corporates who need personnel at the bottom levels. The portal will provide the main competencies needed for the position, and the offer will give the required details including academic courses or actual projects which will help the students fulfill those requirements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
            <h2>Mentoring and Webinars</h2>
            <p>The platform will include webinars and mentoring programs by industry specialists, listing practical skills to further prepare students.</p>
        </div>
